In this speech, Vice President Mike Pence addresses the Christians United for Israel summit in Washington, D.C. He thanks Pastor John Hagee for his leadership, praises President Donald Trump as a great friend of Israel, and highlights the strong alliance between the United States and Israel. Pence discusses Trump's accomplishments in reviving the American economy and rebuilding the military. He also emphasizes the administration's support for Israel, including recognizing Jerusalem as its capital, shutting down the PLO office in Washington, and withdrawing from the Iran nuclear deal. Pence condemns anti-Semitism and criticizes Democrats who have made anti-Israel remarks. He also discusses the crisis at the southern border and the need for secure borders and a fixed immigration system. Pence concludes by expressing faith in the enduring bond between the American and Israeli people.